    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>EBay, the largest Internet auction company, said the intermittent technical problems that have hampered its Web site for the last two weeks might continue for another 10 days. The company posted an apology for the problems on the site, explaining that they stemmed from a system upgrade that eBay began Aug. 2. The problems caused some features to be inaccessible and others to function slowly.</p>
        <p>Laurie J. Flynn (NYT)</p>
      </block>
